Configuration types and file I/O utilities.

{1 Synopsis}

This module defines the configuration system for the SML-to-OCaml converter,
including conversion flags, file paths, and I/O operations. It provides the
{!Common.CONFIG} module type used to parameterize the backend and other
conversion components.

{1 Key Components}

- Configuration record with input/output paths and verbosity levels
- Conversion flags for controlling name transformations
- File I/O utilities for reading SML source and writing OCaml output
- Default configuration values

